Kayode Oyero Ebonyi State Governor, Dave Umahi, has tested positive for the novel coronavirus disease. This was contained in a statement he personally signed on Saturday. Umahi, who said some of his aides also tested positive for the virus, noted that they remained asymptomatic but have since self-isolate themselves in compliance with the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control protocols. READ ALSO: I earned more as a professor than as minister – Pantami He also directed his deputy, Kelechi Igwe, to take over the administration of the state while advising residents to take all precautions outlined by health authorities to curb the spread of the virus. The PUNCH had earlier reported that the governor sent in his samples after some government officials tested positive for the virus.